---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
---

<Layout 
  title="Terms & Conditions | CronGen" 
  description="Read our terms and conditions of use. CronGen is a free open-source utility provided as-is, without warranty of any kind."
>
  <!-- Decorative Top Mesh Gradient -->
  <div class="mesh-gradient" aria-hidden="true"></div>

  <Header />

  <!-- Main Content Layout -->
  <main id="main-content" class="relative z-10 max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16 md:py-24 space-y-12">
    
    <!-- Header -->
    <section class="space-y-4">
      <span class="inline-flex items-center px-2.5 py-0.5 rounded-full text-xs font-mono font-medium bg-link/10 text-link border border-link/20">
        Terms of Service
      </span>
      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-extrabold text-white tracking-tight">
        Terms & Conditions
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xs font-mono text-mute">Last updated: July 2, 2026</p>
    </section>

    <!-- Terms Statements -->
    <section class="space-y-6 text-xs sm:text-sm text-body leading-relaxed">
      <div class="space-y-2">
        <h2 class="text-base font-bold text-white tracking-tight">1. Acceptable Use</h2>
        <p>
          CronGen is a free online tool designed for software developers, devops engineers, and system administrators. You are welcome to use the generated schedules for any personal, educational, commercial, or enterprise infrastructure automation setups. You must not attempt to disrupt or abuse the service's web server.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-2">
        <h2 class="text-base font-bold text-white tracking-tight">2. Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
        <p>
          The service is provided **"as is" and "as available"** without warranty of any kind, either express or implied, including but not limited to the warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, or non-infringement. While we aim to evaluate schedule sequences as accurately as possible, parser and timezone nuances vary across systems. You are solely responsible for verifying the accuracy of any cron expressions before deploying them to live servers.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-2">
        <h2 class="text-base font-bold text-white tracking-tight">3. Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>
          In no event shall the author or contributors of CronGen be held liable for any damages, losses, costs, or claims (including but not limited to server downtime, misfired processes, database loss, or administrative overhead) arising from the use or inability to use this web utility.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-2">
        <h2 class="text-base font-bold text-white tracking-tight">4. Modifications to Terms</h2>
        <p>
          We reserve the right to update or modify these Terms & Conditions at any time without prior notice. Continued use of this website constitutes acceptance of the modified terms.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
